"Kondratyev K.Ya.","On an International Framework Convention on Climate Change: Global climate change in the context of global change",1992,"Il Nuovo Cimento C","15","1",,"87","97",,,10.1007/BF02507774,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-51649142875&partnerID=40&md5=537f872169975d5646e34c30340f7bdc","Institute of Lake Reseach of the Academy of Sciences, Sevastyanov Str. 9, St. Petersburg, 196199, Russian Federation","Kondratyev, K.Ya., Institute of Lake Reseach of the Academy of Sciences, Sevastyanov Str. 9, St. Petersburg, 196199, Russian Federation","The report prepared by the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) for the Second World Climate Conference contains well-weighted assessments of the present-day state of climate studies and of the possible consequences of climate change. Since IPCC's report is supposed to be a basis for working out an International Framework Convention on Climate Change, an analysis has been made of a number of drawbacks in the consideration of the biosphere as an interactive component of the climatic system, as well as of socio-economic impacts of biospheric changes on climate change. Some thoughts have been expressed on the key components of a convention on climate change. © 1992 Società Italiana di Fisica.","Meteorology",,,,,,,"(1990) Climate Change. The IPCC Scientific Assessment, p. 365. , J. T., Houghton, G. J., Jenkins, J. S., Ephrau, Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Borisenkov, E.P., Kondratyev, (1988) Carbon Dioxide and Climate, p. 320. , Gidrometeoizdat, Leningrad; Kondratyev, (1987) Itogi nauki i tekhniki (Meteorol. Climatol.), p. 314. , VINITI, Moscow; Kondratyev, (1992) Global Climate Processes, , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; (1984) The Global Climate, p. 235. , J. T., Houghton, Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Kondratyev, Kozoderov, V.V., Fedchenko, P.P., (1990) Biosphere: Methods and Results of Remote Sensing, p. 224. , Nauka, Moscow; Kondratyev, Kotliakov, V.M., (1991) Izv